WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:25.914 --> 00:27.913
Our top story: The ozone hole...

00:28.023 --> 00:29.898
that devastated Brazil
last summer...

00:29.999 --> 00:31.942
is apparently wintering
in Springfield.

00:32.040 --> 00:33.489
Whoo! Springfield rocks!

00:33.590 --> 00:35.556
Residents are advised
to stay inside...

00:35.665 --> 00:38.753
unless you wear sunscreen
or are very, very hairy.

00:38.860 --> 00:40.803
Experts recommend a class nine...

00:40.903 --> 00:43.272
or Robin Williams level
of hair coverage.

00:43.373 --> 00:45.339
<i>[ Milhouse]
Help! Somebody!</i>

00:45.449 --> 00:47.392
[ Whimpering ]

00:48.841 --> 00:52.627
[ Whimpering ]
Let me in, for the love of-

00:52.729 --> 00:56.279
- [ Groaning ]
- Are you okay?

00:56.385 --> 00:57.766
<i>I've been better.</i>

00:59.021 --> 01:02.278
- Oh, I am so bored.
- [ Groans ]

01:02.381 --> 01:05.110
I can't wait till we're teenagers.
Then we'll be happy.

01:05.214 --> 01:07.707
Well, we could play
Clam Traffic Jam.

01:07.817 --> 01:09.984
Or The Game of County Seats.

01:11.835 --> 01:14.530
Aw, the zoning disk is warped.

01:14.635 --> 01:17.196
All right! Silly String!

01:18.391 --> 01:20.592
[ Laughs ]
Look. You're Milhouse.

01:20.697 --> 01:24.280
Who wets their bed now, Milhouse?
[ Laughs ]

01:24.590 --> 01:25.774
I'll be in my room

01:26.466 --> 01:28.539
It's got to be something fun in my
parents closets

01:29.032 --> 01:30.217
You want to dress up like ladies?

01:30.909 --> 01:34.302
Uh, wouldn't that
make us kind of fruity?

01:34.400 --> 01:36.803
What's the matter?
Scared you might like it?

01:36.904 --> 01:39.004
I'll show you who's scared.

01:39.112 --> 01:43.087
Oh, wow. This really hides my thighs.
[ Purrs ]

01:43.196 --> 01:45.599
[ Both Laughing ]

01:47.084 --> 01:50.341
[ Together]
Sisters are doing it for themselves

01:50.444 --> 01:52.443
<i>- [ Knocking ]
- [ Homer] Hey, why is this door locked?</i>

01:52.551 --> 01:55.247
<i>- Oh, no. It's Dad. [ Groans ]
- [ Bone Cracks ]</i>

01:55.352 --> 01:57.228
[ Groans ]

01:57.329 --> 01:59.822
[ Gasps ]
What's going on?

01:59.931 --> 02:02.986
And I want a non gay explanation!

02:03.094 --> 02:05.856
Uh, we're drunk.
Really drunk.

02:05.960 --> 02:09.116
- Oh, thank God!
- [ Groaning ]

02:10.143 --> 02:13.366
- [ Beeping ]
- Clear.

02:13.470 --> 02:14.941
Why are you doing that?

02:15.051 --> 02:16.927
Oh, it's good for the batteries.

02:17.028 --> 02:19.195
Now, I'm afraid your son
has cracked his coccyx.

02:19.301 --> 02:21.008
[ All Laughing ]

02:21.112 --> 02:23.943
Sorry. How long
will he take to recover?

02:24.045 --> 02:27.032
He'll have to wear this
fanny cast for quite some time.

02:27.141 --> 02:30.588
But don't worry, son.
It fits snuggly under your clothes.

02:30.699 --> 02:33.394
Do all these people
have to watch me?

02:34.915 --> 02:37.318
Now, son, this is
a teaching hospital...

02:37.419 --> 02:40.811
which is why I equipped the seat
of your cast with a viewing window.

02:40.911 --> 02:43.247
- Oh, my. Oh, now that's something.
- He should exercise more.

02:44.534 --> 02:46.477
[ Grunting ]

02:48.158 --> 02:50.224
Uh, little help.

02:51.913 --> 02:53.789
<i>[ Skinner]
Bart, stop fooling around.</i>

02:53.890 --> 02:55.889
Principal Skinner,
I thought public schools...

02:55.999 --> 02:58.930
were required to have
access ramps for the disabled.

02:59.029 --> 03:02.511
Technically, yes, but the building costs
would be astronomical.

03:02.619 --> 03:04.989
<i>Did I hear the word ''astronomical''?</i>

03:05.091 --> 03:10.089
If so, my construction outfit, Valdazo
Brothers Olive Oil, is poised to help.

03:10.197 --> 03:11.870
No, no, no, no.
We're not building anything.

03:11.976 --> 03:15.233
How can you say that when
construction has already begun?

03:15.336 --> 03:17.537
<i>- [ Tires Screech ]
- [Jackhammer Rounding ]</i>

03:17.642 --> 03:19.518
How did those trucks
get here so fast?

03:19.618 --> 03:23.729
In order to avoid certain legal complications,
the trucks are always rolling.

03:23.835 --> 03:27.451
<i>- Now for the groundbreaking ceremony.
- [ Camera Shutter Clicks ]</i>

03:27.557 --> 03:29.398
<i>[Jackhammer Rounding ]</i>

03:29.501 --> 03:31.837
Good Lord. Do we really
need all those ramps?

03:31.939 --> 03:35.454
Who's to say? Does a peacock
need all those feathers?

03:35.562 --> 03:38.291
- Look. You're getting a little philosophical for me.
- I suppose so.

03:38.395 --> 03:40.888
They say it happens
in the autumn years.

03:40.998 --> 03:42.997
- Be that as it may-
- Get your hand off my car.

03:43.106 --> 03:44.982
- [ Whimpers ]
- [ Squeaks ]

03:45.082 --> 03:46.992
This is a proud day.

03:47.091 --> 03:51.865
Now, when people ask if we're in compliance with
the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1975...

03:51.967 --> 03:55.292
<i>I can say, ''We are closer
than ever before!''</i>

03:55.393 --> 03:57.134
[ Cheering ]

03:57.238 --> 03:59.473
Thank you. To inaugurate
our ramp system...

03:59.576 --> 04:03.788
here's the first of what I hope will be
many disabled students, Bart Simpson.

04:03.892 --> 04:06.295
I'm proud of you, boy.

04:06.396 --> 04:08.888
- What the-
- Bart, where's your wheelchair?

04:08.998 --> 04:12.221
Don't need it anymore. Doctor says
my butt bone's stronger than ever.

04:12.325 --> 04:14.886
[ Grunting ]
Ta-da!

04:18.288 --> 04:20.849
Well, at least we're prepared
for the new millennium.

04:25.568 --> 04:27.904
My God! The whole thing's
made of breadsticks!

04:28.006 --> 04:31.061
And paint and shellac.
It's all itemized in this bill.

04:32.025 --> 04:33.935
$200,000? Are you mad?

04:34.034 --> 04:36.966
I don't get mad.
I get stabby.

04:37.065 --> 04:39.065
[ Grumbles ]

04:39.173 --> 04:43.576
The good news is we need no longer fear
vicious mob reprisals.

04:43.686 --> 04:45.719
[ Horn Honks ]

04:49.714 --> 04:54.555
But due to lack of funds,
Springfield Elementary is closed forever.

04:54.656 --> 04:56.655
[ All ]
Yea!

04:56.764 --> 04:58.797
Oh, you're cheering now.
But someday you'll-

04:58.906 --> 05:00.546
Yea!

05:00.651 --> 05:04.369
- I'm just gonna stop trying.
- Yea!

05:06.911 --> 05:09.741
- [ Chattering ]
- How could you close the school?

05:09.842 --> 05:12.301
- What will become of our kids?
- Where are the refreshments?

05:12.412 --> 05:14.973
You keep asking me that,
and I keep telling you over there.

05:16.793 --> 05:18.759
[ Clears Throat ]
As for the school...

05:18.869 --> 05:22.283
we are exploring various options
to raise the $200,000 we need.

05:22.393 --> 05:25.021
I've got a motor home I never use.
Maybe we should raffe it off.

05:25.128 --> 05:28.251
- Maybe you should shut up.
- Well, I- Okay.

05:28.356 --> 05:31.411
We could try selling liquor.
Uh, I'm doing great.

05:31.519 --> 05:33.787
Please, sir.
Put some shoes on.

05:33.890 --> 05:35.395
What? You don't like my bags?

05:35.504 --> 05:37.447
[ Groans ]
People, these are all good ideas-

05:37.547 --> 05:40.501
No, they're not.
They're terrible, terrible ideas.

05:40.610 --> 05:43.834
You're right. It's hopeless.
No one has that kind of money.

05:43.938 --> 05:46.666
What about Mr. Burns?
Maybe he'll help us out.

05:46.770 --> 05:50.128
Forget it. He releases the hounds
on every charity that comes to his door.

05:50.229 --> 05:53.453
Feed the Children. Save the Whales.
Even Release the Hounds.

05:53.557 --> 05:58.364
Uh, well, maybe we can pry open his wallet
with a slick, professional pitch.

05:58.465 --> 06:00.408
A school play!

06:03.077 --> 06:07.581
<i>Welcome to the world premiere
of The Nice Man Giveth.</i>

06:07.689 --> 06:09.957
- [ Groans ] Focus!
- It's a play, sir.

06:11.510 --> 06:14.903
Hmm. Which one of these is the salt?

06:15.002 --> 06:18.326
Too bad I'm an idiot
'cause my school closed. Oh, well.

06:19.252 --> 06:20.700
No! That's the rat poison!

06:20.800 --> 06:23.292
<i>And freeze.</i>

06:23.402 --> 06:26.457
Now, who in Springfield
will eat the poisoned broth?

06:26.564 --> 06:28.474
Oh, it could be anyone.

06:28.574 --> 06:30.248
Even Mr. Burns.

06:30.353 --> 06:32.263
This play really speaks to me.

06:33.383 --> 06:35.619
[ Imitating Siren Wailing ]

06:35.722 --> 06:37.688
<i>I can't take Mr. Burns
to the ''hospital''...</i>

06:37.798 --> 06:39.931
'cause I'm too dumb to read a map.

06:40.038 --> 06:42.474
Oh, why did my school have to close?

06:42.575 --> 06:44.708
- Hmm.
- [ Wheels Squeaking ]

06:46.363 --> 06:50.081
Hello. I'm Dr. Stupid.
I'm going to take out your liver bones.

06:50.184 --> 06:52.127
[ Grunts ]
Oops. You're dead.

06:52.227 --> 06:53.866
I never liked that Dr. Stupid.

06:55.916 --> 06:59.993
- Mr. Burns, I'll be honest.
We had a hidden agenda tonight.
- [ Gasps ] No.

07:00.100 --> 07:03.582
The holiday season is approaching,
and these children need a school.

07:03.691 --> 07:08.195
Charity, eh? Yes. I'd be more
than happy to-

07:08.302 --> 07:10.369
[ All Screaming, Groaning ]

07:10.476 --> 07:12.442
Oh, it's doing that thing again.

07:12.552 --> 07:16.438
<i>[ Man Announcing ]
We now return to Dónde Está Justice.</i>

07:16.538 --> 07:19.234
<i>El Ford Escort
que me vendió es un limón.</i>

07:19.338 --> 07:23.550
<i>No, no, no, no. No es un limón.
Es un carro fuerte.</i>

07:23.654 --> 07:26.978
<i>Hmm. Limón. Fuerte.
Limón. Fuerte. Limón-</i>

07:27.079 --> 07:29.539
<i>;Ay, ay, ay, ay, ay!
;.Mi estómago!</i>

07:29.649 --> 07:33.558
<i>[ Groans ]
Daytime TV is muy estúpido.</i>

07:33.668 --> 07:35.509
<i>Hey, our school's
on TV.</i>

07:35.611 --> 07:38.442
Springfield elementary
has reopened its doors.

07:38.544 --> 07:39.723
[ Both Gasp ]

07:39.828 --> 07:42.356
I'm with Jim Hope
of Kid First Industries...

07:42.463 --> 07:45.327
which has generously stepped in
to educate our children.

07:45.428 --> 07:48.123
That's right, Kent. You know,
when public schools drop the ball...

07:48.228 --> 07:51.620
it's up to the private sector to fall on
that fumble and run for the end zone.

07:51.720 --> 07:54.449
Will you be replacing the current teachers
and administrators?

07:54.553 --> 07:58.563
Very much so, Kent. But they've already received
an extremely generous severance package.

07:58.671 --> 08:03.344
Valencia? [ Scoffs ]
These are juice oranges.

08:03.448 --> 08:05.750
Howdy, children. I'd like to
welcome you back to school.

08:05.853 --> 08:08.088
- [ All ] Boo!
- You know what? I agree.

08:08.192 --> 08:10.101
- [ All ] Wha-
- Your old school was boring.

08:10.201 --> 08:13.817
That's why it failed, right? Well, we're not
gonna make you memorize facts and dates.

08:13.923 --> 08:19.157
No, no, no. I'm gonna find out
what you really love in life and teach to that.

08:19.260 --> 08:21.427
- What are you passionate about, partner?
- Boogers.

08:21.533 --> 08:23.532
[ All Laughing ]

08:23.642 --> 08:26.203
Boogers! [ Laughs ]
That was great.

08:26.309 --> 08:29.791
- You know, humor is a sign of intelligence.
- You're not mad?

08:29.900 --> 08:33.482
Hey, I'm here to make sure
that you get a kick out of education.

08:33.589 --> 08:36.150
- Hi-yah!
- [ All Cheering ]

08:36.258 --> 08:38.784
He's rekindled
my love affair with books.

08:38.893 --> 08:40.308
<i>- [ Thumping ]
- [ Bart Grunting ]</i>

08:40.408 --> 08:43.136
[ Grunting ]

08:43.241 --> 08:46.330
Check it out. I'm breaking
books at a sixth grade level.

08:46.437 --> 08:49.098
- [ Grunts ]
- Get 'em, boy. Hit those smart-ass books.

08:49.204 --> 08:51.080
Why don't you kick some books, Lisa?

08:51.181 --> 08:53.348
Bart broke all my books.

08:53.453 --> 08:56.778
You know what our homework is?
Find a toy and bring it to class.

08:56.880 --> 08:58.161
Boy, that sounds fun.

08:58.263 --> 09:00.330
I know. But I'm still
not gonna do it.

09:02.216 --> 09:06.102
Since Christmas is coming soon, I thought
we could talk about our favorite toys.

09:06.202 --> 09:08.078
Milhouse, what have you got there?

09:08.179 --> 09:10.706
My busy box.
It's got everything.

09:10.815 --> 09:13.016
Vroom, vroom, vroom!

09:13.120 --> 09:14.996
I'm calling Daddy.

09:15.096 --> 09:18.050
Good for you, not being bound
by the recommended age.

09:18.160 --> 09:21.776
What are you talking about?
Oh, geez.

09:21.883 --> 09:23.882
How about the rest of you?

09:23.991 --> 09:26.024
What do you like about
those toys of yours?

09:26.132 --> 09:28.266
- They're special.
- They're challenging.

09:28.372 --> 09:32.450
<i> [ ''Pop Goes The Weasel''
Intro Repeating ]</i>

09:35.059 --> 09:38.968
Very good. Now I want you all
to imagine the perfect toy.

09:39.078 --> 09:41.740
- What would it be like?
- It should be soft and cuddly.

09:41.846 --> 09:44.800
- Yeah. With lots of firepower.
- Its eyes should be telescopes.

09:44.909 --> 09:48.919
No. Periscopes. No. Microscopes!
Can you come back to me?

09:49.027 --> 09:50.993
It should be full of surprises.

09:51.102 --> 09:54.034
- It should never stop dancing.
- [ Martin ] It should need accessories.

09:54.133 --> 09:58.244
Now that's market research you can take
to the bank- the money bank.

09:58.350 --> 10:01.214
I just wish those second-graders
would stop jerking us around.

10:02.731 --> 10:06.123
- Fun toys are fun.
- Well said, Ralph.

10:06.223 --> 10:08.592
But we're trying to come up with
a name for a toy.

10:08.694 --> 10:10.367
- Mrs. Fun?
- Not bad.

10:10.473 --> 10:13.371
- Fun?
- Ralph, there are no right or wrong answers...

10:13.470 --> 10:15.637
<i>but if you don't pipe down,
I'm giving you an ''F.''</i>

10:15.743 --> 10:17.652
The before teacher yelled at me too.

10:17.753 --> 10:20.212
No one's yelling.
We're just brainstorming names.

10:20.322 --> 10:22.198
Lisa, any ideas?

10:22.298 --> 10:24.264
Oh. Uh, a name with fun?

10:24.374 --> 10:27.788
Um, Fungus, Funzo, Attila the Fun.

10:27.899 --> 10:31.156
- Lisa, are you doing math?
- Uh,just a few Venn diagrams.

10:31.259 --> 10:33.135
There's more under her chair.

10:34.948 --> 10:37.150
[ Chuckles ]
Lisa in trouble.

10:37.255 --> 10:39.198
<i>Ha! The ''ironing'' is delicious.</i>

10:39.296 --> 10:41.666
<i>- The word is ''irony.''
- Huh?</i>

10:41.768 --> 10:43.935
Don't you think there's
something weird going on here?

10:44.040 --> 10:46.443
We spent all day
selecting fabric swatches...

10:46.544 --> 10:49.408
and then our guest speaker
was Phil from Marketing.

10:49.509 --> 10:54.316
Alls I know is I'm gettin' straight A's,
and that ain't not bad.

10:54.418 --> 10:56.686
- [ Laughs ]
- That's not funny.

10:56.789 --> 10:58.665
Huh?

11:03.443 --> 11:04.656
[ Gasps ]

11:12.964 --> 11:14.839
They're spying on us.

11:14.940 --> 11:16.816
Why would they do that?

11:16.917 --> 11:18.826
<i>- [ Computerized Male Voice] I see you.
- [ Gasps ]</i>

11:20.705 --> 11:22.648
Give me a hug.

11:22.747 --> 11:25.342
[ Screams ]

11:29.317 --> 11:31.262
This better be important, Lisa.

11:31.361 --> 11:33.238
I left Ralphie alone in the bathtub.

11:33.339 --> 11:36.139
[ Ralph ]
Daddy, I'm ready to get out now. Over.

11:37.956 --> 11:40.125
This broom closet
is not what it seems.

11:40.231 --> 11:43.884
It's a secret surveillance room
guarded by a tiny evil robot.

11:43.990 --> 11:46.823
[ Groans ] Is this gonna be like
one of those horror movies...

11:46.925 --> 11:49.094
where we open the door
and everything's normal...

11:49.200 --> 11:52.393
and we think you're crazy,
but then there really is a killer robot...

11:52.497 --> 11:55.554
and the next morning you find me
impaled on a weather vane?

11:55.663 --> 11:57.541
Is that what this is, Lisa?

11:57.641 --> 12:00.406
To be fair, not all
evil robots are killers.

12:00.510 --> 12:04.828
Listen, when you see what's inside this-
[ Gasps ]

12:04.928 --> 12:07.390
I don't understand.
I could swear it was right here.

12:07.500 --> 12:09.905
Yeah, right, mop top.
And I'm Ed Sullivan.

12:10.006 --> 12:13.423
<i>[ Clears Throat ]
''Really big show.'' No, no. I can do it better.</i>

12:13.534 --> 12:15.248
<i>[ Imitating Ed Sullivan ]
''Really big show. Really big.'' That's it.</i>

12:15.248 --> 12:16.235
<i>[ Imitating Ed Sullivan ]
''Really big show. Really big.'' That's it.</i>

12:17.033 --> 12:21.875
Hello folks! That's the end of
Krusty's  Non- Denominational Holiday Funfest

12:21.975 --> 12:24.999
I want to thank
my guests, Téa Leoni...

12:25.108 --> 12:27.075
<i>- Beck-
- ?? [ Hip-hop Drumbeat ]</i>

12:27.185 --> 12:30.209
<i>- The Dixie Chicks-
- Merry Christmas, y'all.</i>

12:30.318 --> 12:33.713
<i>and Patrick Ewing as the genie.</i>

12:33.813 --> 12:36.544
So have a merry Christmas,
happy Hanukkah...

12:36.648 --> 12:39.908
<i>''kwazy'' Kwanzaa, a tip-top Tet...</i>

12:40.012 --> 12:42.969
and a solemn, dignified Ramadan.

12:43.078 --> 12:46.406
Now a word from my god, our sponsor.

12:48.024 --> 12:50.228
<i>- [ Computerized Male Voice] I see you.
- [ Gasps ]</i>

12:51.190 --> 12:54.517
- Aw!
- Give me a hug.

12:54.619 --> 12:57.216
[ Gasps ]
That's the doll that attacked me.

12:57.323 --> 13:00.549
<i>[ Man Announcing ]
This Christmas, everybody wants Funzo.</i>

13:00.653 --> 13:03.486
<i>''Funzo''? I said that name in class.</i>

13:03.588 --> 13:07.208
<i>- Funzo's soft and cuddly.
- With lots of firepower.</i>

13:07.313 --> 13:09.225
- Ow. [ Groans ]
- Yes!

13:09.325 --> 13:11.034
Ha-ha!

13:11.139 --> 13:13.634
<i>[ Announcer]
Funzo! Funzo! Funzo!</i>

13:13.744 --> 13:16.903
<i>If you don't have Funzo,
you're nothin'.</i>

13:17.008 --> 13:18.919
Mom, I know what
I want for Christmas.

13:19.020 --> 13:21.751
Bart, they lied to us.
Instead of giving us an education...

13:21.855 --> 13:24.294
they tricked us
into designing a toy.

13:24.394 --> 13:26.395
- Aren't you outraged?
- No.

13:26.505 --> 13:30.394
- But if you're gonna throw a spaz, I'll come with.
- Good. Saddle up the bikes.

13:30.494 --> 13:33.057
[ Electricity Crackling ]

13:34.418 --> 13:36.386
Get down.
Security guard.

13:39.364 --> 13:41.859
Hey. It's Gary Coleman.

13:41.969 --> 13:44.431
<i>But the menu said
''galaxy of prawns.''</i>

13:44.540 --> 13:47.002
Three prawns are hardly a galaxy.

13:47.113 --> 13:50.632
What do you mean your hands are tied?
Let me talk to Mr. Quan.

13:50.739 --> 13:54.528
<i>- I want to see how this turns out.
- The phone's not even plugged in.</i>

13:54.631 --> 13:56.509
All right.
You listen to me, Quan.

13:56.609 --> 13:58.644
Hang on. I got another call.

13:58.752 --> 14:01.483
Yes, Mr. President.
I can be in Washington right away.

14:05.150 --> 14:08.905
You people took advantage
of trusting school children.

14:09.007 --> 14:10.546
How did you get past Gary Coleman?

14:10.656 --> 14:13.613
Let's just say he's a few prawns
short of a galaxy.

14:13.722 --> 14:15.667
[ Shouting ]

14:17.349 --> 14:20.047
I'm sorry, Gary.
There's no longer a place for you here.

14:20.152 --> 14:21.827
What you talkin' about, Miss Nagel?

14:21.932 --> 14:25.193
That is so adorable.
You're rehired.

14:25.296 --> 14:28.387
Sucker! I knew exactly
what she was talkin' about.

14:30.406 --> 14:32.351
[ Snoring ]

14:33.935 --> 14:36.532
Lisa, I know you're mad,
but just for a damn minute...

14:36.639 --> 14:39.370
try to see this from
a product positioning standpoint.

14:39.474 --> 14:41.610
Do you have any idea how much
pressure we're under...

14:41.716 --> 14:44.280
to come up with
a new Furby or Tickle Me Elmo?

14:44.388 --> 14:47.749
And thanks to you,
Funzo is the first doll designed by children...

14:47.849 --> 14:50.345
for children, with all the profits
going to children.

14:50.454 --> 14:53.580
- Really?
- Yeah. Well, we're all somebody's children.

14:53.686 --> 14:56.384
But hey, we did screw you a little.
So here's a free Funzo.

14:56.488 --> 14:59.906
- Deal! Ha.
- Oh, brother.

15:00.082 --> 15:01.994
<i>And I want Funzo's Dream Fortress...</i>

15:02.094 --> 15:04.859
Funzo's Lower Back Pain Chair...

15:04.963 --> 15:07.728
Funzo's European
Voltage Converter-

15:07.832 --> 15:11.092
- Why not get three?
- [ Gasps ] Three it is.

15:14.723 --> 15:16.960
Thanks, Funzo.
You rock.

15:17.064 --> 15:20.650
All righty.
[ Dance ]

15:20.757 --> 15:22.859
It's always a party with Funzo.

15:22.966 --> 15:27.081
I admit it's kind of cute.
But it'll never take the place of Malibu Stacy.

15:27.187 --> 15:29.065
[ Stops ]

15:31.440 --> 15:33.936
[ Gasps ]
Did you see that?

15:34.045 --> 15:36.810
Yeah. Funzo makes playtime fun!

15:38.200 --> 15:40.167
[ Krusty's Voice ]
Hey, kids. It's- [ Groaning ]

15:40.277 --> 15:42.716
Hey. Why is it
destroying other toys?

15:42.817 --> 15:45.312
They must have programmed it
to eliminate the competition.

15:45.422 --> 15:47.557
- You mean like Microsoft?
- Exactly.

15:47.664 --> 15:49.732
Come on, Bart.
We've gotta warn everyone.

15:49.840 --> 15:53.291
[ Dance Music, Vocalizing ]

15:56.632 --> 15:58.341
Boycott Funzo!

15:58.445 --> 16:00.750
He's a toy-killing machine!

16:00.853 --> 16:02.764
[ Chuckles ]
That shy little imp?

16:02.865 --> 16:06.192
I have a flower for 'ou.

16:06.294 --> 16:08.699
- [ All ] Aw.
- Oh, man. I gotta get me one of those.

16:08.800 --> 16:11.330
Hey, I'm not waiting
till the store opens.

16:11.437 --> 16:13.315
[ All Shouting ]

16:13.416 --> 16:17.531
Wow. Only 22 seconds from
muttering to door smash.

16:17.636 --> 16:21.425
That projects to a profit
of... $370 million.

16:21.527 --> 16:24.090
I'd still sleep a little easier
if I saw some trampling.

16:24.198 --> 16:26.436
- [ All Shouting ]
- Ow, ow, ow! Hey! Ow!

16:26.539 --> 16:28.574
Now why would you
wear cleats to a store?

16:28.683 --> 16:29.930
[ Glasses Clink ]

16:30.035 --> 16:31.912
Well, I guess that's it.

16:32.013 --> 16:34.947
Come Christmas Eve,
there'll be a Funzo under every tree.

16:35.046 --> 16:36.991
Unless-

16:39.036 --> 16:41.408
- So who am I beating up?
- Nobody.

16:41.509 --> 16:44.465
You're just gonna break into everyone's
house and steal their favorite toy.

16:44.575 --> 16:46.453
Thus saving Christmas.

16:46.554 --> 16:49.814
Now let's see. This'll make
three Christmases I saved...

16:49.917 --> 16:51.795
versus eight I ruined.

16:51.896 --> 16:54.830
- Two were kind of a draw.
- Dad. Dad, you're driving on the sidewalk.

16:54.930 --> 16:56.807
<i>- Oh! Sorry.
- [ Cat Screeches ]</i>

16:57.864 --> 16:59.741
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

17:00.930 --> 17:04.516
Joy to the world
The Lord is come ?

17:04.623 --> 17:08.479
Let earth receive her king
- [ BellJingles ]

17:08.579 --> 17:11.772
- ? Let every ??
Season's greetings.
- Peace out.

17:14.580 --> 17:16.526
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

17:17.714 --> 17:20.906
Silent night

17:21.012 --> 17:26.082
- [ Loud Crash ]
- [ Singing Louder] ? Holy night ?

17:26.188 --> 17:29.414
- [ Screaming ]
- ? All is calm ?

17:29.518 --> 17:33.801
All is bright
Rou-

17:36.541 --> 17:39.105
[ Dance ]
- All righty.

17:39.212 --> 17:42.968
Writhing Funzos in my sack

17:43.070 --> 17:46.466
Makes me happy
Makes me hurt my back

17:46.566 --> 17:48.443
Just dump 'em in the fire, Dad.

17:48.544 --> 17:50.748
Yes. The madness ends here.

17:50.852 --> 17:53.257
Oh! If I had a nickel
for every time I've heard that.

17:53.358 --> 17:55.303
[ Grunting ]

17:57.183 --> 17:59.151
- [ All Whirring ]
- ?? [ Dance ]

17:59.260 --> 18:02.656
I'm very mad at 'ou.
[ Groans ]

18:05.196 --> 18:06.545
[ All Gasp ]

18:09.548 --> 18:12.078
Well, what do we have here?

18:12.186 --> 18:14.221
<i>Looks like the biggest
rip-off since Webster.</i>

18:14.362 --> 18:17.319
[ Gasps ]
Please, Mr. Coleman. We can explain.

18:17.429 --> 18:20.689
<i>- I'm listening.
- Your toy company is evil.</i>

18:20.792 --> 18:24.378
Well, isn't it possible for an evil company
to make people happy?

18:24.485 --> 18:27.182
Are you saying the end
justifies the means?

18:27.288 --> 18:29.356
That's a very glib interpretation.

18:29.464 --> 18:31.465
Hey! Don't talk
to my sister that way.

18:31.574 --> 18:34.598
No, Bart. He's right.
I did oversimplify.

18:34.707 --> 18:37.866
Perhaps. But let's not
get bogged down in semantics.

18:37.971 --> 18:40.073
I think what Lisa
meant to say is-

18:40.180 --> 18:43.114
<i>[ Man Narrating ]
And so, Gary Coleman and the Simpsons...</i>

18:43.214 --> 18:46.047
<i>argued long into the night.</i>

18:46.148 --> 18:48.643
<i>And then, as day broke...</i>

18:48.753 --> 18:51.844
<i>the spirit of the season
entered their hearts.</i>

18:51.952 --> 18:56.527
Let's just agree that the commercialization
of Christmas is, at best, a mixed blessing.

18:56.634 --> 18:57.522
Amen.

18:57.623 --> 18:59.568
- Indeed. Amen.
- Yeah. Amen.

18:59.668 --> 19:01.972
Love!

19:02.074 --> 19:04.210
Hey. Look out!
[ Shouts ]

19:09.790 --> 19:12.320
Well, there's something
you don't see every Christmas.

19:12.429 --> 19:15.689
Hey. It is Christmas.
We better get home.

19:18.660 --> 19:22.146
Hey, Dad. What do you think of-
[ Whispering ]

19:25.452 --> 19:28.286
Um, uh, Mr. Coleman,
I've been thinking.

19:28.387 --> 19:33.424
<i>Uh, my wife always makes too much
stuffing and sweet ''potaters'' and all.</i>

19:33.531 --> 19:35.409
And- Oh, heck.

19:35.509 --> 19:37.679
Would you like to
spend Christmas with us?

19:37.785 --> 19:41.900
No way. I'm having Christmas
at George Clooney's house.

19:42.005 --> 19:44.905
- Gary.
- All right. I'll come.

19:46.259 --> 19:49.283
<i>[ Narrator]
And Gary Coleman was as good as his word.</i>

19:49.392 --> 19:53.405
<i>As for old Mr. Burns, he was visited
by three ghosts during the night...</i>

19:53.513 --> 19:58.021
<i>and agreed to fund the school with
some money he found in his tuxedo pants.</i>

19:58.130 --> 20:00.299
Thank you. Thank you.
Humbug.

20:00.405 --> 20:05.115
<i>[ Narrator] While Moe, seeing what the world
would be like if he had never been born...</i>

20:05.219 --> 20:10.290
<i>pulled his head out of the oven and replaced it
with a plump Christmas goose.</i>

20:10.395 --> 20:12.340
[ Grunts ]
Happy holidays there.

20:12.440 --> 20:14.609
[ All ]
Merry Christmas, Moe.

20:14.715 --> 20:18.042
Uh, listen. I kind of banged up
that Jeep in the driveway.

20:18.144 --> 20:19.650
What you talkin' about, Moe?

20:19.760 --> 20:21.929
[ All Laughing ]

20:22.036 --> 20:25.555
What you talkin' 'bout, everyone?

